dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c McCullum b Oram 40 (27b 3x4 3x6 57m) SR: 148.14

dismissalComment.html: The Big cat has departed. Oram has struck. Oram saw Sehwag charging out like a speeding truck and quickly shortened the length. Sehwag tried to adjust by going for a pull shot but ended up top edging it high to point region where McCullum takes it. Entertainment over. Or does it? Yuvraj steps out.

headshotImage.caption: Yuvraj Singh headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: Yuvraj Singh headshot

dismissalComment.html: The Black Caps are rocking here. Ryder slips in a full length delivery, just like the previous two, and Yuvraj went for his square drive but ended up edging it behind.

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: And Jesse Ryder has got rid of the Indian captain. As he has done through this little knock, Dhoni moved down the wicket and towards off stump. As he has done all through, Ryder kept his calm and got the ball to cut in from outside off. Dhoni went for the on-the-up push-drive but got a thick inside edge. Good persistent bowling gets the result.

headshotImage.caption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Ryder's day out. "I am a fan" say the banners from the Kiwis. Another delivery cutting into the batsman and Yusuf plays all around it and gets a fatal inside edge.. Timber! This is super stuff from Ryder and NZ.

dismissalComment.html: Scott Styris you beauty! There was lot of confusion initially about who is going to take it but Styris does it in the end. Raina went for a big swing, but got under the ball too much and the ball ballooned towards mid-on. Styris  ran in from midwicket - the mid-on was sent back earlier - his captain was at mid-off. Yours or mine? It looked both were going to stand and watch but Styris moved in the end and dived to hold a tumbling catch. Two down. Wickets and runs. Where is Bill Lawry I say.

dismissalText.commentary: Harbhajan Singh run out (Vettori/Oram) 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: Vettori pulls off a smart piece of fielding, nothing smart about the Indians' running. It was driven well to the right of mid-off where Vettori ran to a make a fine diving stop. Harbhajan started to run initially but didn't want it on second thoughts but Rohit kept going across like a run-away train. THe throw comes to non-striker's end and Harbhajan gave himself up.

dismissalText.commentary: Zaheer Khan run out (Oram/Vettori) 5 (10b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: Another run out. Another messy running. It was dabbed to short third man, Zaheer didn't want a run, Rohit wanted - it was the non-striker's call - and Zaheer responded late. Very late. Gone. Stranded. NZ fans are smiling at last.

dismissalText.commentary: Jesse Ryder b I Sharma 63 (49b 6x4 4x6 70m) SR: 128.57

dismissalComment.html: Ishant gets his man with little bit of help from Ryder himself. It was a short of length delivery angling away from Ryder who tried to punch it through extra cover but edged it back to his stumps. He is very disappointed, swings his bat in the air over the stumps and shakes his head as he walks off. Ishant doesn't celebrate much. A very fine entertaining knock comes to an end.

commentTextItems.html: Majestic pull to bring up the win. It was the bouncer and Martin Guptill stood up tall to unfurl a spanking pull. New Zealand have won the game and by doing that, have made everybody look forward to the Test series.

commentPostTextItems.html: Nagging bowling. Violent but controlled aggression while batting. Game over. Congrats NZ. Hang on for the post-match presentation.
Man of the Match Jesse Ryder : "Things are going all right at the moment. The confidence is high. I am looking forward to play in the Test series.

Vettori: We are looking forward to Test series. It should be competitive. Thanks to the crowd for coming in." And he adds with a smile, "Some of you supported us!" ha! Huge Indian-dominated audience there.
Dhoni: I would like to thank my team for playing well through the series. Sorry {to the crowd who roar] for disappointing you guys in the final match.
That's it from us. On behalf of Sanjay, our scorer, this is Sriram Veera, signing off.  See you in the Test series. Ta!

commentTextItems.html: Guptill take a bow. Bloody entertaining way to bring up your fifty. He moved his front foot out and biffed the full length delivery over wide long-on. The white ball kept sailing into the night sky.
on the middle and leg, worked past square leg for couple of runs.

commentTextItems.html: That bottom hand is working overtime. It was on the middle, may be middle and leg, but Taylor's shuffle meant it was easy pickings for him. And he whipped it to midwicket boundary.
fuller, driven to mid-off
drags back the length and shifts the line to outside off, steered to backward point
he has killed this one. He shuffles to the off stump and swings the full length delivery over cow corner. Ala Dean Jones. Bloody Marvellous.
very nice. It was full in length and Taylor uses the bottom hand to power the lofted drive and whips it over wide midwicket
pushes it off the front of his hand, full and sliding in, driven down to long-on

dismissalComment.html: Scott Styris you beauty! There was lot of confusion initially about who is going to take it but Styris does it in the end. Raina went for a big swing, but got under the ball too much and the ball ballooned towards mid-on. Styris  ran in from midwicket - the mid-on was sent back earlier - his captain was at mid-off. Yours or mine? It looked both were going to stand and watch but Styris moved in the end and dived to hold a tumbling catch. Two down. Wickets and runs. Where is Bill Lawry I say.

dismissalComment.html: The Big cat has departed. Oram has struck. Oram saw Sehwag charging out like a speeding truck and quickly shortened the length. headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: And Jesse Ryder has got rid of the Indian captain. As he has done through this little knock, Dhoni moved down the wicket and towards off stump. Good persistent bowling gets the result.

dismissalComment.html: Ishant gets his man with little bit of help from Ryder himself. It was a short of length delivery angling away from Ryder who tried to punch it through extra cover but edged it back to his stumps.
